description: 1-, 2-, 3- ... digit numbers in alphabetical order in French (incorrect version, see A187876 for the correct version).
comments: This sequence has been preserved in the state it was in the printed Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences but is unfortunately incorrect. For instance, 80 is "quatre-vingts", so comes after quatre-vingt-cinq, not before. For a corrected version see A187876. __Olivier GÃ©rard__, Jul 04 2012
references: N. J. A. Sloane and Simon Plouffe, The Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences, Academic Press, 1995 (includes this sequence).
crossrefs: Cf. A187876 for the correct version, giving a few 3-digits numbers as well.
